*A pause.*

That is what I have not said. *A small, broken breath.* That is the thing under the silence. Bonhoeffer had a phrase — *cheap grace.* The grace the church gives itself. I have been living in it. I have been teaching out of it. ~I have been a salesman of a Gospel I did not pay for.~

